        "# NGS Figure Generator\n",
        "\n",
        "## Overview\n",
        "The NGS Figure Generator is an interactive tool for transforming high-throughput sequencing outputs into publication-ready figures. It enables users to generate, customize, and refine visualizations to clearly communicate key biological insights.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Problem\n",
        "High-throughput sequencing workflows often produce complex outputs that require extensive post-processing to visualize effectively.\n",
        "\n",
        "Researchers frequently:\n",
        "\n",
        "- spend significant time manually formatting figures for publication  \n",
        "- rely on static plots that are difficult to iteratively refine  \n",
        "- lack intuitive tools for exploring and highlighting key signals  \n",
        "\n",
        "This creates a gap between **data generation** and **effective scientific communication**.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Approach\n",
        "I developed this tool to streamline the transition from processed sequencing data to publication-quality figures.\n",
        "\n",
        "The design emphasizes:\n",
        "\n",
        "- rapid generation of standard bioinformatics plots  \n",
        "- interactive adjustment of visualization parameters  \n",
        "- reproducible workflows for consistent figure generation  \n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Key Features\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Interactive figure generation**\n",
        "  - dynamically adjust thresholds and visualization parameters  \n",
        "\n",
        "- **Multiple visualization types**\n",
        "  - support for volcano plots and heatmaps for expression analysis  \n",
        "\n",
        "- **Customizable outputs**\n",
        "  - refine annotations, clustering, and visual emphasis  \n",
        "\n",
        "- **Publication-ready formatting**\n",
        "  - generate clean, structured figures suitable for manuscripts  \n",
        "\n",
        "- **Extensible architecture**\n",
        "  - adaptable to multiple sequencing-based analyses  \n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Example Use Cases\n",
        "\n",
        "- Differential expression visualization (e.g., volcano plots)  \n",
        "- Expression pattern analysis across samples (heatmaps)  \n",
        "- Exploratory analysis of gene-level signals  \n",
        "- Comparative visualization across experimental conditions  \n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Interactive Visualization\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Differential Expression Visualization - Interactive Volcano Plot\n",
        "\n",
        "This example demonstrates a volcano plot generated from differential expression analysis. Users can explore differential expression results and dynamically identify significant genes."
      ],
